sentence: In consumer stocks news, Royal Caribbean Cruises ( RCL ) Friday reported EPS above street views, and nearly met revenue expectations.
Royal Caribbean traded up 3.90% pre-bell to 98.38 inside a 52-week trading range of $61.35 to $97.60.

Procter & Gamble ( PG ) shares were slightly lower in recent pre-market trade after the company reported mixed fiscal Q1 results compared to estimates while foreign exchange rates and divestments are expected to lead to a decline in sales in 2016.
And Whirlpool Corporation ( WHR ), an appliance manufacturer, reported Q3 results that topped the Street view on ongoing earnings per share as revenues fell short of estimates.
The company reported Q3 net earnings of $235 million, or $2.95 per diluted share, compared to $230 million, or $2.88 per diluted share, reported for the same prior-year period.
